Methods</span><hr size=1> Well, you asked me to come post so here I am.  Most of the solo tactics I have used have already been discussed.  But I have a few minutes so I'll just go over them again. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have soloed <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> most</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of my exp from 52 to 55(almost 55 now) in Dreadlands.  I am pretty sure you can do that same from 48 to 55.  <br>
<br>
I normaly log on full mana and health.<br>
Buff up:  Sow/wolfform, Barbcoat, Skin, Str of Nature, Call of Earth, Str, Agi, Call of Sky, Dmg Shield.  <br>
<br>
With the level 49 spells, mobs take 16dmg each time they hit you.  Level 50(call of earch) adds 4 more, for a total of 20 per hit.  That's probably around 400-600 dmg on the mob per fight(assuming they hit me about 20 times for an avg of 45dmg per hit).  WAY more mana efficient than any other spell we have.<br>
<br>
I normaly pull Ragers, Petrafied Cocks, Voracious Brutes, and Ravishing doggies.  I never fight spiders, I don't like the damage shield on them and I'm too lazy to dispell it.<br>
<br>
I will normaly pull with an arrow and let it follow me to my spot(takes forever if you pull with snare).  First thing I'll do is root it when we get to the solo spot.  Next is snare, then Tolans Arms(stinging swarm).  I'll normaly poke him with a few arrows while root is still on, then engage for melee.  Normaly by the end of the fight I've used about a bubble of mana and 2 bubbles of health(with the exception of ravishing drolvargs which normaly about double those numbers).<br>
<br>
I'll normaly repeat this 2-3 times if I can before the dmg shield and call of sky wear off.  If on the 3rd fight I get too low and oom, I'll finish them with arrows.<br>
<br>
One thing I do that saves a little bit of time is I cast call of sky and the dmg shield while I'm pulling, not before...this way they last through as many fights as possible.  Also, don't cast other buffs(skin, nature str, call of earth etc) while Oom.  Wait till you have enough mana to fight again, then cast the buffs.  Same reason, they will last through more fights, there is no reason to be buffed during down time.<br>
<br>
With tracking you should never have a problem getting the mob you want(low to mid blue every time).<br>
<br>
One of the advantages with fighting in Dreadlands is there are normaly people willing to cast clarity(I normaly offer 5plat per shot and find someone to keep getting me each round) and heal you during downtime.  I never ask for heals, but I normaly sit by Karnors while I'm medding and someone will just run by and heal or chloro.  That's a huge help, but don't expect it or it wont happen. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Well, that's my short guide to soloing DL.  Heh, fear kiting animals is a blast, try it in Eastern Wastes too -- walrus, griffons, dogs, can't remember the others, but do NOT try to fear kite a manticore hehe.<br>
<br>
I hope this gives you some new ideas.  Have fun. <p><a href=http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=6277>Ranarius Spiritarrow</a><BR><a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsentinelsoftunare>Sentinels Of Tunare</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uasanifiadhaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asani Fiadhaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/21/01 11:59:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/shieldtr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Ranger Solo Methods</span><hr size=1> And either camp a Fungi Tunic or save your lootses to buy one. They're a godsend for any class that wants to solo and is allowed to wear them. <p><center><a href=http://www.silentredemption.org><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/images/friends/asanisig.jpg ></a></center>
